The paper deals with the problem of approximating a minimum routing cost spanning tree in a distributed setting, which involves message passing and limited bandwidth. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-categories. The problem also involves graph theory and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to the Networked Systems (cs.NI), Algorithms (cs.AL), and Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories.
